E4Plus1.uk.description: Grumpy George: Karen and Christian admit that they have 'no clue' how to run their British pub in Texas - and it shows. Can Gordon give this mishmash of ideas a sense of direction? (S9 Ep8)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Kids Are All Fight: When Homer finds an old roll of film and has it developed, the family take a trip down memory lane to when Bart and Lisa were always fighting. (S26 Ep19/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Bull-E: Bart is picked on at the school dance, so Marge convinces Springfield's authorities to pass anti-bullying legislation. But then Homer's arrested for victimising Ned. (S26 Ep21/22)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: My Sister, My Sitter: Lisa starts a new career as a babysitter. All is going well, until Marge and Homer employ her to look after Bart and Maggie... (S8 Ep17/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Coming to Homerica: When nearby Ogdenville's unemployed come to Springfield looking for jobs, Mayor Quimby shuts the town's borders and enlists private citizens to guard them. (S20 Ep21/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Goldbergs
E4Plus1.uk.description: A Chorus Lie: Adam's voice breaks right when he lands the lead role in the school musical. (S3 Ep2)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Live Football: Mali v Senegal
E4Plus1.uk.description: The first quarter-final at the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations. Can the irresistible force of the Lions of Teranga overcome the immovable object that is Mali?

E4Plus1.uk.title: Live Football: Cameroon v Morocco
E4Plus1.uk.description: The second quarter-final at the Africa Cup of Nations. Clashes don't come much more heavyweight than Indomitable Lions v Atlas Lions... This is surely the hosts' toughest test so far.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Will Is Home Alone: Will's mum goes on a weekend away with an old friend. Will is left home alone and the boys take advantage of the situation. It's all fun until the morning. (S3 Ep5/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Camping Trip: Will draws on his scouting experience to cope with the last trip he's organised for the boys before they go their separate ways. But the others are unprepared. (S3 Ep6/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: First Day: Smash hit comedy about four teenagers. Will (Simon Bird), whose parents have divorced, must move to a new area and change from private to comprehensive school. (S1 Ep1/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Bunk Off: Will, Simon, Jay and Neil bunk off school. They go to Neil's house to get drunk, and Simon has a vodka-induced romantic revelation about his childhood sweetheart Carli. (S1 Ep2/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Naked Attraction
E4Plus1.uk.description: A celebration of Naked Attraction's very best naughty bits, revisiting times when the show broke new dating ground, including when trans woman and celebrity Lauren Harries entered a pod.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Naked Attraction
E4Plus1.uk.description: A celebration of Naked Attraction's very best naughty bits, revisiting the good, the bad and the kinky, from a polyamorous couple and a three-time picker to food fetishes and whipped cream.

E4Plus1.uk.title: First Dates
E4Plus1.uk.description: Neuroscientist and self-confessed geek Michael is yet to find someone with the right kind of chemistry. His date Hannah hopes that her dream man exists outside her romance novels. (S12 Ep3)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Will Is Home Alone: Will's mum goes on a weekend away with an old friend. Will is left home alone and the boys take advantage of the situation. It's all fun until the morning. (S3 Ep5/6) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Camping Trip: Will draws on his scouting experience to cope with the last trip he's organised for the boys before they go their separate ways. But the others are unprepared. (S3 Ep6/6) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: Sal's Pizza: When Peralta's favourite restaurant burns down, the fire marshal assumes that the owner is the prime suspect. A virus hits the precinct's computers. (S1 Ep9)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Brooklyn Nine-Nine
E4Plus1.uk.description: Thanksgiving: Santiago hosts a Thanksgiving dinner at her apartment for her colleagues, but it risks becoming a holiday disaster. (S1 Ep10)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Treehouse of Horror VIII: Mayor Quimby insults the French government, who launch a neutron bomb in retaliation. Homer escapes the blast and finds himself alone in Springfield. (S9 Ep4/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Realty Bites: Marge takes a job with Lionel Hutz's estate agency, but begins to question her morals when she has to try to sell the infamous Murder House to Ned Flanders. (S9 Ep9/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Miracle on Evergreen Terrace: When Bart destroys the family's Christmas tree and presents, his lies about a burglar stealing them spiral out of control. (S9 Ep10/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Lego Masters Australia
E4Plus1.uk.description: Over the Falls: The Grand Master teams must make a build which tells a story both as it goes over a waterfall, and as it crashes on the rocks below. (S5 Ep2) [SL]

E4Plus1.uk.title: Don't Tell the Bride
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Northern Soul One: Nathan loves music and Stoke-on-Trent, so when bride-to-be Beccie gives him free rein to organise their wedding, he plans Northern Soul nuptials.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: Whanex?: While preparing a presentation for his students about future goals, Cam must contend with a bully at the school. Jay has technical trouble during a video conference. (S10 Ep13)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Modern Family
E4Plus1.uk.description: We Need to Talk About Lily: Phil thinks he's found Pepper's dream home. Mitch and Cam get invited to an exclusive event. (S10 Ep14)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Paw Patrol: The Movie
E4Plus1.uk.description: (2021) Family animation. The plucky pups head to the city to foil dastardly Mayor Humdinger's latest plot. But can Chase overcome his fear of the big smoke and be the hero everyone needs?

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: 3 Southern Girls: When a car accident left her son fighting for his life, Gabi was forced to close her traditional restaurant for over a month. Can Gordon help launch a comeback? (S9 Ep5)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Ramsay's Kitchen Nightmares USA
E4Plus1.uk.description: Kings Blu Jam: With debts mounting, and a 'toxic' dynamic between owner Connie and her manager and daughter Justin, can Gordon turn things around at Kings Blu Jam Caf in Texas? (S9 Ep6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Homer the Whopper: Homer is chosen to appear in a superhero movie and the film studio hires a celebrity trainer (guest star Seth Rogen) to help him develop a muscular physique. (S21 Ep1/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Bart Gets a 'Z': When Edna Krabappel confiscates her students' phones, Bart gets revenge by spiking her coffee with alcohol, and Principal Skinner fires her for being drunk. (S21 Ep2/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: The Great Wife Hope: The male citizens of Springfield become obsessed with the brutal sport of Ultimate Punching, and Marge ends up getting challenged to step into the ring... (S21 Ep3/23)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: My Sister, My Sitter: Lisa starts a new career as a babysitter. All is going well, until Marge and Homer employ her to look after Bart and Maggie... (S8 Ep17/25)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Simpsons
E4Plus1.uk.description: Simpsons Tall Tales: A hobo regales the family with unique takes on classic American tales starring the Simpsons as Connie Appleseed, Paul Bunyan and Tom Sawyer. (S12 Ep21/21)

E4Plus1.uk.title: Live Football: Algeria v Nigeria
E4Plus1.uk.description: The third AFCON 2025 quarter-final pits defensive excellence against attacking verve, with Algeria, who've conceded just one goal so far, taking on tournament high scorers Nigeria.

E4Plus1.uk.title: Live Football: Egypt v Cte...
E4Plus1.uk.description: ...d'Ivoire: The final AFCON 2025 quarter-final pits Mo Salah's Egypt against reigning AFCON champions Cte d'Ivoire, for whom Manchester United's Amad Diallo is in blistering form.

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Thorpe Park: After passing his driving test, Simon takes the boys on their first road trip: a day out at Thorpe Park, where Will disgraces himself on the roller coaster. (S1 Ep3/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Will Gets a Girlfriend: Will sees that going to a mixed-sex school isn't so bad when he pulls the most popular girl in the year above. But he alienates his hard-won new friends. (S1 Ep4/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Caravan Club: The boys call Jay's bluff and go to the Camber Sands meeting of the Caravan Club to see if it really is a massive sex party. Jay's dad gives them advice about sex. (S1 Ep5/6)

E4Plus1.uk.title: The Inbetweeners
E4Plus1.uk.description: Xmas Party: It's the end of term and Will has been voted chairman of the Christmas prom committee, so he ropes in Simon, Jay and Neil to help get things organised. (S1 Ep6/6)

Film4.uk.title: LA Confidential
Film4.uk.description: (1997) Curtis Hanson's thriller of cops and corruption set in 1950s LA - with Kevin Spacey, Guy Pearce, Russell Crowe and Kim Basinger. Based on James Ellroy's detective novel.

Film4.uk.title: No Exit
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Thriller. A recovering addict ends up stranded at a remote visitor centre in a snowstorm with four strangers, then finds a kidnapped girl in the car park. Question is: who did it?

Film4.uk.title: Blackbird
Film4.uk.description: (2019) Kate Winslet, Susan Sarandon, Sam Neill and Mia Wasikowska star in this drama about a terminally ill mum who gathers her family one last time before she plans to take her own life.

Film4.uk.title: Broken Arrow
Film4.uk.description: (1950) Western starring James Stewart. A gold prospector, tired of reprisal killings between whites and Native Americans, offers a truce to the Apaches' leader. But tensions resurface.

Film4.uk.title: D-Day the Sixth of June
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Wartime romance set against the background of the D-Day landings, starring Robert Taylor and Dana Wynter. A married American officer embarks on an affair with English nurse.

Film4.uk.title: The Spoilers
Film4.uk.description: (1955) Western. Anne Baxter, Jeff Chandler and Rory Calhoun star in a tale of fortune-seeking and treachery on the untamed Alaskan frontier.

Film4.uk.title: Jubal
Film4.uk.description: (1956) Western with Glenn Ford, Ernest Borgnine, Rod Steiger and Valerie French. A cowboy is given a job by a rancher, sparking lethal jealousy in a colleague and desire in the boss's wife.

Film4.uk.title: Instant Family
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Comedy. Mark Wahlberg and Rose Byrne star as a couple whose orderly lives are disrupted when they foster three kids. Based on director Sean Anders' own experience.

Film4.uk.title: FRIGHTENERS, THE (1996)
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Peter Jackson's comedy horror stars Michael J Fox as a psychic investigator in a town that has more ghouls and ghosties than you can shake a spirit stick at. But is he a fraud?

Film4.uk.title: Darkman
Film4.uk.description: (1990) Liam Neeson and Frances McDormand star in Sam Raimi's crime-fighting action-fantasy. A vengeful scientist invents a synthetic skin that lets him change his appearance...

Film4.uk.title: Earwig
Film4.uk.description: (2021) Period body-horror. In post-war Europe, an anxious man makes an edental girl frozen-saliva teeth in a dreary apartment. But now he must prepare her for life outside their four walls.

Film4.uk.title: The Caine Mutiny
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Oscar-nominated Humphrey Bogart, in one of his finest roles, stars in Edward Dmytryk's gripping drama as Captain Philip Queeg, in charge of a US Navy minesweeper during the war.

Film4.uk.title: Film4 Interview Programmes:...

Film4.uk.title: Roman Holiday
Film4.uk.description: (1953) Audrey Hepburn won her only Oscar in this romance as a bored princess who runs away from her duties and meets an American journalist (Gregory Peck), who shows her Rome.

Film4.uk.title: How Green Was My Valley
Film4.uk.description: (1941) Walter Pidgeon, Maureen O'Hara and Roddy McDowall star in John Ford's multi-Oscar-winning period drama set in the mining communities of the South Wales Valleys of the 19th century.

Film4.uk.title: A Knight's Tale
Film4.uk.description: (2001) Modern swashbuckling medieval action adventure starring Heath Ledger, Shannyn Sossamon and Paul Bettany. A lowly squire jousts his way to the top, with help from Geoffrey Chaucer.

Film4.uk.title: The Last Stand
Film4.uk.description: (2013) Thriller starring Arnold Schwarzenegger, Johnny Knoxville and Forest Whitaker. A small-town sheriff and his inexperienced staff take on a drug cartel boss who's fleeing to Mexico.

Film4.uk.title: Legion
Film4.uk.description: (2010) Apocalyptic action-horror starring Paul Bettany. God's patience runs out and He decides to wipe humanity from the face of the Earth. Can a rebel archangel save us?

Film4.uk.title: Dead Presidents
Film4.uk.description: (1995) Crime drama set in the Bronx of the 70s, starring Larenz Tate. To support his young family, a Vietnam veteran is driven to take part in the daring robbery of an armoured truck.

Film4.uk.title: Jingle All the Way
Film4.uk.description: (1996) Brian Levant's festive all-action comedy. Arnold Schwarzenegger is on a mission to get his son (Jake Lloyd) the must-have Christmas toy, Turbo Man. But it's sold out everywhere...

Film4.uk.title: Patrick
Film4.uk.description: (2018) Feel-good British family comedy. Sarah's (Beattie Edmondson) chaotic life gets even more complicated when she inherits a naughty pug from her nan.

Film4.uk.title: Turner & Hooch
Film4.uk.description: (1989) Comedy-thriller starring Tom Hanks. A cop investigates a murder to which there's just one witness: Hooch, a slobbering, beer-drinking French mastiff, who now needs 24/7 protection.

Film4.uk.title: Prince Valiant
Film4.uk.description: (1954) Swashbuckling adventure. One of King Arthur's courtiers, the Viking Prince Valiant (Robert Wagner) uncovers the evil Sir Brack's (James Mason) plot to kill the king. Can he foil him?

Film4.uk.title: I, Robot
Film4.uk.description: (2004) Sci-fi thriller with Will Smith. In 2035, a technophobic cop investigates a crime that may have been perpetrated by a robot. Can he keep an open mind?

Film4.uk.title: The Adjustment Bureau
Film4.uk.description: (2011) Romance meets sci-fi thriller. Matt Damon and Emily Blunt star as a politician and a dancer who begin to suspect that a shadowy group of men are interfering with their lives.

Film4.uk.title: Pearl
Film4.uk.description: (2022) Ti West's exuberant retro horror and prequel to X. Mia Goth is Pearl - a twisted Dorothy who wants to dance up the yellow brick road to movie stardom. Can a seedy projectionist help?

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Road Rage: More comic adventures with the great Rowan Atkinson as Inspector Fowler. Patricia decides to spend her leave with a tribe of road protesters known as the Dongers. S2 Ep6

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: The Thin Blue Line
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: The Green-Eyed Monster: Laughs at the expense of the boys in blue with the beany Rowan Atkinson. Will Fowler finally propose to Patricia? And will she accept him if he does? S2 Ep7

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Froghall to Bugsworth Basin: Robbie Cumming explores the English canal network. A low canal tunnel in Staffordshire proves to be problematic and Robbie helps out a stranded boater. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Marple to Huddersfield: Robbie Cumming continues across the Pennines from Marple to Huddersfield, where his journey is hampered by a fallen tree and a leaking lock pound. S1 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Danube River, Austria: Robson Green is in Austria hiking along the stunning Wachau Valley, following the incredible blue Danube river. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ferrari Rep/Figaro/3 Tractors: Derek is on the road to pick up a funky little Nissan Figaro and a sublime Ferrari 250 GT tribute car, and Paul gets to try out his spanking new Scania T Cab. S9 Ep7
